Project Name: EC2 with SSM + Nginx Custom Page

1. Services Used

EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud): Instance launch ‡§ï‡§∞‡§£‡•á

IAM (Identity & Access Management): Role ‡§§‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§∞‡•Ç‡§® attach ‡§ï‡§∞‡§£‡•á

SSM (AWS Systems Manager): Agent install ‡§ï‡§∞‡•Ç‡§® EC2 manage ‡§ï‡§∞‡§£‡•á

VPC + Security Group: HTTP (80) inbound traffic allow ‡§ï‡§∞‡§£‡•á

2. IAM Role Creation

AWS Console ‚Üí IAM ‚Üí Roles ‚Üí Create Role

Trusted Entity: AWS Service ‚Üí Select EC2

Permissions Attach:

‚úÖ AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore (Required)

(Optional) AmazonS3FullAccess

(Optional) AmazonEC2RoleforAWSCodeDeploy

(Optional) AmazonSSMFullAccess

Role Name: EC2-SSM-Role

Click Create Role

3. Attach IAM Role to EC2 Instance

Go to EC2 ‚Üí Instances

Select your instance ‚Üí Actions ‚Üí Security ‚Üí Modify IAM Role

Select EC2-SSM-Role ‚Üí Save

4. Launch EC2 Instance

AMI: Ubuntu 20.04/22.04

Instance Type: t2.micro (Free Tier)

Key Pair: Proceed without key pair (SSM ‡§µ‡§æ‡§™‡§∞‡§£‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§∏‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§®‡•á key ‡§Ü‡§µ‡§∂‡•ç‡§Ø‡§ï ‡§®‡§æ‡§π‡•Ä)

Network:

Public IP ‚Üí Enable

Security Group ‚Üí Add Inbound Rule ‚Üí HTTP (80) ‚Üí Source: 0.0.0.0/0

IAM Role: Attach ‚Üí EC2-SSM-Role

5. Install SSM Agent (Ubuntu)

‡§ú‡§∞ agent online ‡§®‡§∏‡•á‡§≤ ‡§§‡§∞ manually install ‡§ï‡§∞‡§æ.

# Update packages
sudo apt-get update -y

# Install SSM Agent
sudo snap install amazon-ssm-agent --classic

# Enable service
sudo systemctl enable snap.amazon-ssm-agent.amazon-ssm-agent.service

# Start service
sudo systemctl start snap.amazon-ssm-agent.amazon-ssm-agent.service

# Check status
systemctl status snap.amazon-ssm-agent.amazon-ssm-agent.service


‚úÖ ‡§Ü‡§§‡§æ ‡§§‡•Å‡§Æ‡§ö‡§æ instance SSM ‚Üí Managed Instances ‡§Æ‡§ß‡•ç‡§Ø‡•á ‡§¶‡§ø‡§∏‡§æ‡§Ø‡§≤‡§æ ‡§π‡§µ‡§æ.

6. Install Nginx + Custom Page (via SSM Run Command)

Systems Manager ‚Üí Run Command ‚Üí Run a command ‚Üí Document: AWS-RunShellScript

Commands:

# Update packages
sudo apt-get update -y

# Install Nginx
sudo apt-get install nginx -y

# Enable Nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx

# Start Nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx

# Remove default Nginx page
sudo rm -rf /var/www/html/index.nginx-debian.html

# Create custom page
echo "Welcome to My Custom Nginx Page - SSM + EC2" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

